.TH "port_r_mib_pkt" 9 "port_r_mib_pkt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
port_r_mib_pkt \- read dropped packet counts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" port_r_mib_pkt
.BI "(struct ksz_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "int port "  ","
.BI "u32 *last "  ","
.BI "u64 *cnt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
The hardware instance.
.IP "port" 12
The port index.
.IP "last" 12
last one
.IP "cnt" 12
Buffer to store the receive and transmit dropped packet counts.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine reads the dropped packet counts of the port.
Hardware interrupts are disabled to minimize corruption of read data.
